	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You need context, since a single byte includes no extra information as to whether it's used as an opcode, operand, or data, or combination of these.
<br />
<br />1) Disassemble continuously
<br />
<br />2) Emulate game and keep track of which bytes were executed as opcodes

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


